    <subfield code="y">00003 The same potential in terms of  the field $\sigma$ and the canonical inflaton field $\varphi$. One can see, in particular, that the tops of the three  hills in the upper corner of the previous figure become converted into three infinitely long ridges, and the two minima separating them at $\phi = 1$ in Fig. \ref{fig:3} become two inflationary valleys.</subfield>
